		<div class="c-date">
			November 8, 2020		</div>
				<p>As of 2018, there are 30.2 million small businesses operating in the United States. (Source: <a href="https://www.chamberofcommerce.org/small-business-statistics/" rel="nofollow">https://www.chamberofcommerce.org/small-business-statistics/</a>)</p>
<p>22 million of the small businesses in the United States are individually operated, meaning that they have no other employees other than the owner. (Source: <a href="https://www.chamberofcommerce.org/small-business-statistics/" rel="nofollow">https://www.chamberofcommerce.org/small-business-statistics/</a>)</p>
<p>Those who work independently still sell their bodies and minds. So, I would not count them as businesses.<br />
30.2-22=8.2 These 8.2 are buyers of bodies and minds. Many are probably in CA and NY.  I am guessing there is not enough petit bourgeois to support Trump, but I would be interested in seeing % distribution of these people between the two camps. These 8.2 + 22 are probably mostly in serves, the same services that COVID-19 is wiping out. Trump&#8217;s calls to keep &#8216;economy open&#8217; played to that constituency.</p>
				<div class="reply">
