<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-119437" >
	<div class="c-grav"></div>
	<div class="c-body">
		<div class="c-head">
			nihil obstet <span class="c-permalink"><a href="https://www.ianwelsh.net/week-end-wrap-political-economy-november-8-2020/#comment-119437">permalink</a></span>		</div>
		<div class="c-date">
			November 8, 2020		</div>
				<p>Everybody wants a sense of worth.  In the U.S. that&#8217;s always meant getting the trappings of achievement, from more money to a higher status job.  The ptb have defined job status in a way that keeps higher paid jobs to themselves &#8212; jobs that require credentials from elite, expensive institutions.  We must break out of this hierarchical categorizing of people.  Somebody&#8217;s got to pick tomatoes and collect garbage.  Covid-19 has shown who the essential workers really are.  It makes clear how vicious a message is that says, &#8220;You want a better life, get a better job.&#8221;  Let&#8217;s instead remember Debs who said &#8220;I don&#8217;t want to rise from the masses;  I want to rise with the masses.&#8221;</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s quit assigning value to people based on a work hierarchy.  The tomato picker and the garbage collector should make enough money to participate fully in the society, just as each of us should.  Who&#8217;s in the working class is an interesting question for analysis, but it shouldn&#8217;t be considered a real issue in developing decent politics.</p>
				<div class="reply">
					</div>
			</div><!--end c-body-->
