		<div class="c-date">
			November 8, 2020		</div>
				<p>Ever since the Democrats decided to jettison their old coalition (organized labor, racial minorities, etc.) and go after the professional class, the working class has not had a party that served their interests. Workers still voted, of course, but there were no issues on any platform to improve the lot of the working class. So, appeals to their patriotism, their racial bias, their disdain for immigrants (legal and otherwise), etc. were made but no representation on the issue of working people.</p>
<p>So, the question: which party is the party of the working class is simple: neither.</p>
