<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-119447" >
	<div class="c-grav"></div>
	<div class="c-body">
		<div class="c-head">
			Willy <span class="c-permalink"><a href="https://www.ianwelsh.net/week-end-wrap-political-economy-november-8-2020/#comment-119447">permalink</a></span>		</div>
		<div class="c-date">
			November 9, 2020		</div>
				<p>Took me one gatekeeper, and a hand specialist two cortisone shots to &#8216;cure&#8217; my trigger thumb. </p>
<p>I usually ride out pain with some rest-n-rehab researched myself, but it was getting too much to get the thumb moving in the morning.  So glad I was insured at the time, and lucky to get a qualified and ethical specialist.  </p>
<p>Not so lucky with an ear infection, which had been misdiagnosed the first time by an idiotic fake doctor (nurse practitioner) when my own guy (big city clinic) was a month out.  I trusted their recommendation, never again.  She charged the same.  I then had to go in six times to an ENT who wanted the extra business.  That place wound up with major malpractice lawsuits after a fake &#8216;all-star surgeon&#8217; scandal.  It remember when it was once top-notch.</p>
<p>We have no choice but to have the government get involved when medical MBAs and lobbyists ruin the business.</p>
